FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42102
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1780419953
OL,3,C'Oldest' Horizon scandal victim Betty
OL,4,CBrown receives OBE from King
OL,6,FShe ran the Annfield Plain Post Office
OL,7,Fnear Stanley in County Durham with her
OL,8,Fhusband Oswall from 1985 to 2003 and
OL,9,Festimates they lost around #100,000 of
OL,10,Ftheir own money to cover non-existent
OL,11,Fshortfalls.
OL,13,FThe OBE was to recognise her services
OL,14,Fto justice after campaigning for sub-
OL,15,Fpostmasters.
OL,17,FThe Horizon accounting system, run by
OL,18,FJapanese firm Fujitsu, made it appear
OL,19,Fthat money was missing from sub-
OL,20,Fpostmasters' branch accounts.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1780419953
OL,3,C'Oldest' Horizon scandal victim Betty
OL,4,CBrown receives OBE from King
OL,6,FIt is at the centre of the long-
OL,7,Frunning Post Office scandal, which saw
OL,8,Faround 1,000 people wrongly prosecuted
OL,9,Fand convicted throughout the UK
OL,10,Fbetween 1999 and 2015.
OL,12,FMs Brown, who is one of the original
OL,13,Fvictims, took part in the group legal
OL,14,Faction led by Sir Alan Bates against
OL,15,Fthe Post Office.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G3/9
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1780419953
OL,3,C'Oldest' Horizon scandal victim Betty
OL,4,CBrown receives OBE from King
OL,6,FSpeaking to the Press Association
OL,7,Fafter meeting King Charles, Ms Brown
OL,8,Fsaid he was "fully informed" of the
OL,9,Fscandal, adding: "It's a great honour
OL,10,Fthat the King has recognised an
OL,11,Fordinary person trying to do something
OL,12,Fgood in the community.
OL,14,F"What I've said to him was: 'Impress
OL,15,Fon the Prime Minister that there is no
OL,16,Fprice on justice.' The quibbling about
OL,17,Fthe money ` stop it, and finish
OL,18,FHorizon immediately.
OL,26,@pD@MOUpD@\O]qD@ROUvD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G4/9
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1780419953
OL,3,C'Oldest' Horizon scandal victim Betty
OL,4,CBrown receives OBE from King
OL,6,F"He (the King) is as upset about it as
OL,7,Fwe are... I said to him, try telling
OL,8,Fthe Prime Minister and his ministers
OL,9,Fthat money doesn't justify not
OL,10,Finvestigating the case.
OL,12,F"Justice is more than money ` tell
OL,13,Fthem that."
OL,15,FAsked how the King responded, Ms Brown
OL,16,Fsaid: "He took it on board."
OL,18,FBetty previously spoke to ITV Tyne
OL,19,FTees when her compensation claim was
OL,20,Fsettled with the government (2025)
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOUuD@KO]xD@GOUxD@\O]
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G5/9
